title: Porcini Smashed Burger
description: We're taking the classic smashed burger up a notch with porcini powder and a special sauce. The dried mushroom powder gives the meat an even deeper savory flavor. Yum Yum. Yum.

steps.step: For the seasoning: In a small bowl, mix the salt, pepper, and porcini powder.

For the sauce: In another small bowl, combine the  cup mayonnaise, ketchup, cornichons, diced white onion, onion powder, and granulated garlic and stir to combine. Cover and refrigerate if not using right away.

Spread a little mayonnaise on the cut sides of the buns and reserve. Prepare the patties by dividing the beef into 8 equal portions (about 4 oz each) and rolling each portion into a ball. Place the balls on a rimmed baking sheet and sprinkle the tops with about half of the porcini seasoning.
Have handy a large, metal spatula and a 5- to 6-inch square of parchment paper. Preheat 2 adjacent zones on the flat top to medium-high heat and 1 zone to medium-low heat, for 8 to 10 minutes.

Squeeze or drizzle the oil onto the hot cooktop and use the spatula to spread it evenly. Place the buns cut side down on the medium-low zone and toast until golden, about 1 minute. Transfer the rolls to a plate.

Place a beef ball on the medium-high hot surface. If adding white onion, place some on top of the ball. Top the ball with the parchment square, then press down firmly with the spatula to create a thin patty 5 to 6 inches across. Repeat to make the other 7 patties. Cook each patty until nicely browned on one side, about 3 minutes.

Carefully flip the patties, sprinkle with the remaining seasoning, and top with the cheese. Cook, covering the patties with a dome to speed melting if desired, until the cheese is melted, about 1 minute more. Transfer the patties to a clean plate, stacking them to make 4 double patties.

To serve, place a stack of two patties on the bottom bun. Top with some of the red onion and a couple slices of tomato. Spread some special sauce on the top bun, top the burger with it, and take a big bite. Enjoy!

author: James M
